      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LITTLE VESPER (1) looks close to another win after hitting the frame in a 1.5 lengths second (24.72) in a Grade 5 at Goulburn. Won at her only start from this box. Good form should continue. MYSTICAL ETHICS (7) turned in a better run last time to find a minor placing (29.86) at this track behind Bandit Lynne in a Grade 5. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Must be included in calculations. ZIPPING SMEE (6) had a tricky draw last time and although midfield in fourth wasn't far away finishing 3.5 lengths from the winner (30.18). The form from his last run stacks up well. Should be about the mark. SAHARA PEARL (2) is one of the chances after a surprise minor prize last time.",
